I've heard of the method of instrumental variables a lot from
reading the econometrics literature, but it wasn't until recently that
that I began to see how great of a thing it is in the data scientist's toolbox.

The setting is like this. We have a binary treatment $X$ like exposure to an ad,
and we want to understand its effect on an outcome $Y$, like sales.
